To receive Social Welfare assistance in Northern Ireland from April this year onwards, please follow these steps based on whether it’s claimed through Direct Payments Scheme [DPS] system or Self-Service Portal System.
For DPS claims via mail,
You will require Proof-of-Domicile Document such as Birth certificate/Passport/Social Security card; Utility bill with current date stamp showing residential usage;
Proof Of Residence
for example Rent Agreement/Rental Contract/Accommodation Rental Letter etc.; Bank Statement(s)
showing deposit amount received into account during last six months;

Self-service portal users should ensure they’re registered by logging onto https://www.dwp.gov.uk/register/.

